        "created_at": "2021-07-24T19:54:44.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"172272\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"172272\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"172272\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>one seriously has to wonder whether \u201dclassic vintages\u201d are a thing of the past in Burgundy</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Food for thought: <a href=\"https://weather.com/weather/tenday/l/Beaune+21+France+FRXX0392:1:FR\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">10-Day Weather Forecast for Beaune, C\u00f4te-d\u2019Or, France - The Weather Channel | weather.com</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Pretty moist! We just had a lengthy heatwave in Finland (by our standards) while at the same time there were many sub-20C days in Beaune. I guess one can only wonder what is to come of this vintage when it\u2019s all said and done.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Lots of disease pressure! Battling a bit of powdery mildew that just reared its head in my Beaune parcel  <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/8/8600bbd4810d342b8fbd4ffb62b4f0026275fd37.gif\" width=\"38\" height=\"26\" alt=\"[berserker.gif]\" title=\"berserker\" class=\"animated\"></p>",
